-- Istanbul Bourse to Resume Trading After Technical Fault
-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 2012-03-02T11:38:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-02/istanbul-bourse-to-resume-trading-after-technical-fault-1-.html
The  Istanbul Stock Exchange  will
resume trading at 2 p.m. after morning trading was halted
because of a technical fault.  The Exchange will hold a 20-minute opening session from 2
p.m. to 2:20 p.m., to collect orders in the first 15 minutes and
settle prices in the remaining five minutes, and start normal
trading at 2:20 p.m., it said on its website.  The Exchange will also start holding closing sessions for
trading between 5:17 p.m. and 5:30 p.m. from today, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aydan Eksin in Istanbul at 
 aeksin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
